    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="840"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d840">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Russian Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Russian Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Magnolia, Mass.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am directed by cable to request permission to return to Russia, under promise
                    not to take part in the war, for Sublieutenant Bertenson, of the cruiser <hi
                        rend="italic">Aurora</hi>. Admiral Enquist is under orders to submit this
                    request to the local authorities at Manila. Your kind cooperation would be
                    highly appreciated. Sublieutenant Bertenson is a son of the celebrated Doctor
                    Bertenson, physician to His Majesty the Emperor. Another son of his was killed
                    in the battle of Tsu Shima.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rosen.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
